column2: supported sample rate, PLL clock and operation clock combination, this table is indexed by [drf_rate] (need 8-bit). Bit fields stage_active specifies filter setting when in manual mode; for auto mode, only sys_rate and ant_rate are needed.

column9: num of samples per clock, based on ant_rate
column13: each of these 11 bits indicating corresponding filter (from low to high: TBF1, TBF1I/D, TBF2, TBF2I/D, HBF1, FBF1, HBF2, HBF3, HBF4, HBF5 and HBF6) is active or not
column24: data use IQ format or Real at sample I/F. 0: IQ, 1: Real
column35: operation clock, 0:983.04MHz, 1: 1474.56MHz. VHA/V2D/DRF should have same operation clock
